title: THE DINER

description.plain:
“THE DINER” puts the frightening side of fame into perspective, finding Eilish telling a story from the perspective of a stalker, dragging a plot from her past experiences with her many stalkers.

The song, eighth on HIT ME HARD AND SOFT, delves into themes of obsession and desperation. The lyrics show a troubled individual who crosses boundaries just to be with their “lover”, and how they struggle with rejection as well as legal trouble. While she is taking the perspective of a crazed fan of hers, it is possible “THE DINER” could also be read as Billie herself being obsessive over a lover – given the context of the rest of the album.

Eilish has talked about stalkers before, specifically on her 2021 sophomore album Happier Than Ever in tracks like “Getting Older” and “NDA.”
